post_text:
Struthers School Foundation Officers Elected and Funding Requests Approved

Officers elected for the 2019-2020 term of the Struthers School Foundation for Educational Excellence were (left to right) Dave Howard, Treasurer; Drew Hirt, President; Mike Cox, Vice-President and Paul Garchar, Secretary. Also elected was Sheri Noble to serve out the unexpired term of retired Trustee Eric Ryan. This year the Struthers School Foundation has approved funding for just under $25,000 in new student educational opportunities including programs in Greenhouse and Hydroponics Gardening and in Virtual Reality Learning. Supplemental donations by Parisi Excavating, the Struthers Rotary Community Corps, Bigley Landscaping and Ace Hardware assisted in the funding approvals and a very generous financial donation by the Estate of Laddy Fedor was used in part for this year’s funding.

post_text: Another HIGHLY SUCCESSFUL Struthers 4th of July Parade for 2019! Preceded by a 5KRun and The Kristy Taaffe Kids Run, both headed by Foundation Vice-President Mike Cox, the Runs and Parade were documented by our local photographer Frank Marr, lead by the Boy Scouts and Cheerleaders from Struthers Schools. The Grand Marshals were John Grandy and Ron Iarussi, this years' Foundation Hall of Fame inductees and the event was narrated again by Charlie Jasinski. The National Anthem was sung by Candace Campana and the participants and floats were judged this year by School Board president Walter Baber, reporter Kalea Hall, Struthers City Attorney John Zomoida (accompanied by Isabella Zomoida and Kerri Gries) and Megan Mraz. Many thanks once again to Stacey Newyear, John Medvec Jr. and the entire Medvec family for their continued support and to Cat Cercone Miller for once again chairing the Parade Committee for the Struthers School Foundation!
text: Another HIGHLY SUCCESSFUL Struthers 4th of July Parade for 2019! Preceded by a 5KRun and The Kristy Taaffe Kids Run, both headed by Foundation Vice-President Mike Cox, the Runs and Parade were documented by our local photographer Frank Marr, lead by the Boy Scouts and Cheerleaders from Struthers Schools. The Grand Marshals were John Grandy and Ron Iarussi, this years' Foundation Hall of Fame inductees and the event was narrated again by Charlie Jasinski. The National Anthem was sung by Candace Campana and the participants and floats were judged this year by School Board president Walter Baber, reporter Kalea Hall, Struthers City Attorney John Zomoida (accompanied by Isabella Zomoida and Kerri Gries) and Megan Mraz. Many thanks once again to Stacey Newyear, John Medvec Jr. and the entire Medvec family for their continued support and to Cat Cercone Miller for once again chairing the Parade Committee for the Struthers School Foundation!

For those friends who don't know, I am the race director for the Struthers School Foundation 4th of July 5K and Kristy Taaffe Kids run. The 5K was created last year as a way to raise money for the Struthers School Foundation, which provides teaching and educational equipment to Struthers school teachers and students. The Kristy Taaffe Kids run was created to help influence a healthy lifestyle for the students of the Struthers School System and for kids all over the Ytown area. One of the last conversations that I had with my friend Kristy Taaffe was of her desire to create healthy living programs for students through her involvement with the PTA. Thus is why the kids run is named in honor of her. Please register through this link to support the children of our great community. Thank you.
https://runsignup.com/Race/OH/Struthers/StruthersSchoolFoundation4thofJulyParade5K

text: Hall of Fame Banquet

post_text:
The Struthers School Foundation held our Hall of Fame Banquet this evening at the Embassy. We would like to congratulate our Hall of Fame inductees: Attorney Carol Clemente Wagner and Mr. Robert W. Noble Jr. They are both very fine people and very deserving of this honor.

We would also like to thank our Keynote speaker, Mr. Craig Zamary, who is on the faculty of Kent State University and who is also an entrepreneur. Craig gave a very informative presentation and discussed the genesis of the Entrepreneurial Program at the Struthers School System. Our interim school Superintendent, Mr. Pete Pirone provided everyone with a status update on the Entrepreneurial Program and his vision for developing the program going forward.

I would like to thank our Board of Trustees who are very dedicated and work very hard to help the Struthers School System. Our community should be very proud of their efforts. I would a also like to thank them for all of their efforts in pulling the Hall of Fame Banquet together; it takes a lot of work to make this a success.

We are committed in providing ongoing support to the students and teachers in the Struthers School System,” Hollen said.

Grant recipients were teachers at Struthers High School, middle school and elementary school in various subject areas. Funding was provided for 3D printers, an HD Handy Cam, raised garden bed, exercise ball chairs, musical…

Thomas Struthers is with Jenna Cummins and 3 others.
May 24, 2016 at 9:48 PM ·

The Struthers Rotary and Community Corp have announced their 'Service Above Self" scholarship winners for 2016. The Rotary scholarships are awarded to students that have given back to their community. The Community Corp scholarship this year was awarded in honor of Struthers residents Donna Marciano and Frank Marr. The William Comstock scholarship is named for William Comstock, a former Rotarian, Struthers teacher and Board of Education member. It is funded by he Rotary and the Comstock family. Since 1985, the Rotary has awarded $90,000 in scholarships to 150 students. The scholarships are funded by the club's annual Pancake Breakfast held in November

Pic: Scholarship Chairman Tom Baringer, Community Corp President Catherine Miller, Community Corp scholarship winner Carly Szenburn, Makenzie Stewart, Comstock scholarship winner Nick Mozingo, Jenna Cummins, Katelyn Mitcheltree. Not pictured Stefanie Hill

shared_text:
The Struthers School Foundation
December 14, 2015 at 3:24 PM ·

The Struthers School Foundation is proud to announce that we have committed $20,000.00 to help fund an Entrepreneurial Program in partnership with the Struthers School District. It is our understanding that the Struthers School District will be the only school in the Mahoning Valley that will have an Entrepreneurial Program. This program has been in the planning and discussion stage for over a year. "I would like to thank our Foundation Board members for all of their hard work and dedication," said Board President, Dexter Hollen. We are very excited to be able to help bring this program to the Struthers students; this program can be a real game changer.

Counting the $20,000.00 commitment for this program, the Struthers School Foundation will have expended over $100,000.00 in grants on cutting edge educational equipment and opportunities for students in the Struthers School District.

It is our understanding that the Struthers School District will be the only school in the Mahoning Valley that will have an Entrepreneurial Program. This program has been in the planning and discussion stage for over a year. "I would like to thank our Foundation Board members for all of their hard work and dedication," said Board President, Dexter Hollen. We are very excited to be able to help bring this program to the Struthers students; this program can be a real game changer.

Counting the $20,000.00 commitment for this program, the Struthers School Foundation will have expended over $100,000.00 in grants on cutting edge educational equipment and opportunities for students in the Struthers School District.

post_text: The Struthers School Foundation approved and awarded grant applications totaling nearly $15,000.00 for teachers at the Struthers School System at their October 15, 2015 Board Meeting. These grants were made possible thanks to the ongoing support the Foundation receives from the community and a generous donation received from the Cafaro Foundation. Foundation President, Dexter Hollen said "We are committed in providing ongoing support to the students and teachers in the Struthers School System".

post_text: I have just been informed by The Cafaro Foundation that our request for a $5000 grant has been approved! This means we will be awarding even more money to worth grant applicants this coming school year. The grant ask came out of a conversation I had with Cafaro Company representatives on another unrelated matter when we got to talking about foundations and they liked what we are doing and suggested I write in a request for a grant - which, naturally, I did. Thanks to the generosity of the Cafaro Foundation we are $5000 richer!

post_text:
The School Foundation held their election of officers recently and the following officers will take over on September 1: Dexter Hollen - President, JeriLyn Walsh - Vice President, Dan Mamula - Secretary, Dr. Michael Evanson - Treasurer. New trustees will be Chuck Campbell and Catherine Cercone Miller.

The Grand Marshalls for the Struthers 4th of July Parade, which the Foundation sponsors, will be Pete Pirone, Sr. and Pat Ginnetti for his late brother, Dr. Phil Ginnetti who were recently installed in their Foundation Hall of Fame. We hope to see you there!
